h2. Documentation

The "quick start":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Quick+Start provides a
quick introduction to using Watir. The "cheat sheet":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Cheat+Sheet 
provides a handy reference. 

The "tutorial":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Tutorial
provides a detailed, hands-on introduction.

View this  
"succinct summary of the Watir API":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Methods+supported+by+Element
and the provided methods and attributes. You can also review the 
"rdoc":http://wtr.rubyforge.org/rdoc/  -- 
detailed API documentation in Ruby's standard format.

The "FAQ":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/FAQ provides answers to
frequently asked questions.

This "hands-on introduction":http://bpettichord.backpackit.com/pub/1139340 provides exercises using a sample application, which is provided.

There are also several
"articles":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Articles about Watir.

